  "prompt": "How do I avoid an awkward situation after a break up?",
  "response": "Navigating post-breakup interactions can be challenging, but with clear communication, respect, and boundaries, you can minimize awkwardness. Here are some tips to help:\n\n### 1. **Set Clear Boundaries**\n   - Discuss and agree on the level of contact (if any) that feels comfortable for both of you.\n   - Avoid mixed signals\u2014be clear about your intentions and expectations.\n\n### 2. **Take Time Apart**\n   - A \"no-contact\" period can help both parties heal and gain perspective.\n   - Avoid rushing into friendship or frequent interactions immediately after the breakup.\n\n### 3. **Be Respectful and Kind**\n   - Avoid gossiping, blaming, or badmouthing your ex to mutual friends.\n   - If you encounter them unexpectedly, be polite and keep the interaction brief.\n\n### 4. **Avoid Social Media Drama**\n   - Refrain from posting passive-aggressive or emotional updates.\n   - Consider muting or unfollowing your ex temporarily to avoid unnecessary triggers.\n\n### 5. **Plan for Shared Spaces**\n   - If you share mutual friends, work, or social circles, discuss how to handle group events.\n   - Decide if attending the same events is okay or if it\u2019s better to take turns.\n\n### 6. **Stay Mindful of Your Emotions**\n   - Acknowledge your feelings but avoid projecting them onto your ex.\n   - If emotions are still raw, it\u2019s okay to excuse yourself from uncomfortable situations.\n\n### 7. **Communicate When Necessary**\n   - If you need to discuss practical matters (e.g., shared possessions), keep the conversation focused and neutral.\n   - Avoid revisiting the breakup unless both parties are ready for a constructive conversation.\n\n### 8. **Focus on Moving Forward**\n   - Invest time in self-care, hobbies, and building a support system.\n   - The less you dwell on the breakup, the easier it will be to handle interactions.\n\n### 9. **Be Honest with Yourself**\n   - If maintaining contact feels too painful, it\u2019s okay to create distance.\n   - Respect your own needs and prioritize your well-being.\n\n### 10. **Be Prepared for Awkward Moments**\n   - Accept that some awkwardness is inevitable and normal.\n   - Stay calm, keep interactions brief, and focus on moving forward.\n\nBy prioritizing mutual respect and self-care, you can navigate post-breakup situations with grace and maturity, reducing awkwardness over time.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
